Ten lucky readers of the Daily Dispatch will take home one of ten Roto Tanks and one of ten Africa Water & Solar Pumps. To stand a chance of winning simply get a copy of the Daily Dispatch Weekend Edition and fill in the entry form and the weekly question, which is printed in the newspaper every Saturday. Answers to the question will be in an article in the Daily Dispatch. The more times you enter, the better your chances are of winning. Entries can be delivered to Daily Dispatch Beacon Bay, Ink Spot Mthatha, The Rep – Queenstown, OK Foods – Kidd’s Beach, Mdantsane SuperSPAR,  Crossways SPAR, Roto Tanks – Meisies halt, and Africa Water & Solar – Thornvlei Road The winners will be contacted telephonically and announced in the Daily Dispatch newspaper on the following dates: Arena Holdings Group, Roto tanks & Africa Water & Solar Pumps, employees, sponsors, and their immediate families shall not be permitted to enter. This competition is open to all persons 18 years and older. Winners agree to be photographed for the purpose of publicity. The judges’ decision is final, and no correspondence will be entered into. The entry form needs to be an original copy of the Daily Dispatch, no photocopies are allowed. Only completed entry forms will be considered valid and eligible for the draw. The competition closes at 17h00 every second Sunday. No late entries will be accepted. One entry form is equal to one entry; multiple entries per person will be allowed. Winners will be contacted telephonically. Two weekly winners will be announced in the Daily Dispatch newspaper on a Thursday. The prize is non-transferable and not redeemable for cash. By entering, you agree to receive future marketing from Arena Holdings (PTY) LTD. The entrant can opt-out at any time by contacting the relevant parties. E&OE.